Introduction

Yu Jiahn is a South Korean singer and rapper.

In 2016, he was a member and contestant of the pre-debut survival group and show BOYS24. He ranked 5th place and became a member of the final group SKYE, who debuted on October 26, 2017 with the release of the mini album "Carpe Diem".

On September 29, 2023, Yu Jiahn debuted in the group first subunit CoA along fellow member Yeontae with the release of the Japanese single "A New Beginning".

On September 26, 2024, he was revealed as a contestant on JTBC's survival show PROJECT7 starting in October 2024.
